        ('stretching', '', 'static', 'exercisesListImg\One_Knee_To_Chest\0.jpg', 'exercisesListImg\One_Knee_To_Chest\1.jpg', ' Start off by lying on the floor.; Extend one leg straight and pull the other knee to your chest. Hold under the knee joint to protect the kneecap.; Gently tug that knee toward your nose.; Switch sides. This stretches the buttocks and lower back of the bent leg and the hip flexor of the straight leg.', 'beginner', 'compound', 'One Knee To Chest', 'glutes', 'hamstrings;lower back'),
