        ('strength', 'other', 'pull', 'exercisesListImg\Rope_Climb\0.jpg', 'exercisesListImg\Rope_Climb\1.jpg', ' Grab the rope with both hands above your head. Pull down on the rope as you take a small jump.; Wrap the rope around one leg, using your feet to pinch the rope. Reach up as high as possible with your arms, gripping the rope tightly.; Release the rope from your feet as you pull yourself up with your arms, bringing your knees towards your chest.; Resecure your feet on the rope, and then stand up to take another high hold on the rope. Continue until you reach the top of the rope.; To lower yourself, loosen the grip of your feet on the rope as you slide down using a hand over hand motion.', 'intermediate', 'compound', 'Rope Climb', 'lats', 'biceps;forearms;middle back;shoulders'),
